<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="498" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1454,2022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1529,1554]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,443,1529,1554]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Platystigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ranunculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humaita" status="sp. nov.">Humaita</taxonomicName>
, noun in apposition. A reference to the fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[1064,1112,1530,1554]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">type</typeStatus>
was collected in the Forest Reserve of 
<taxonomicName box="[278,378,1565,1590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Platystigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ranunculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humaita" status="sp. nov.">Humaita</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="499" pageId="5" pageNumber="498" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1454,2022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,606,1601,1626]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">
Description of the male 
<typeStatus box="[496,601,1601,1626]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[616,677,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Head</emphasis>
. Labium yellow, face pale blue with pair of small black rounded spots at the lateral part of the labral-clypeal suture. Upper part of head black, with a narrow yellow transverse occipital stripe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1454,2022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1709,1734]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prothorax: pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[560,647,1709,1734]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) black with S-shaped grayish yellow lateral stripe connected with oblong yellow transverse marking on anterior lobe. Posterior lobe bordered with yellow. Propleuron yellowish white with dorsal oblong black spot (
<figureCitation box="[577,662,1781,1806]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Pterothorax: mesepisternum (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1102,1781,1806]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1926]" captionTargetBox="[195,1401,236,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Pterothorax in lateral view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (14); P. martinezi female, holotype (15); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (16); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (17); P. pronoti female, holotype (18); P. quadratum male, holotype (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376930/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) black with middorsal carina yellow. Antehumeral yellow stripe reduced to small subtriangular marking. Posthumeral yellow stripe not reaching lower part of sclerite. Mesepimeron black, metapleuron yellow with black stripe along metapleural suture. Venter with posterior and anterior triangular black spot, latter continued in black midline (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1163,1889,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[280,1335,276,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Venter in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (20); P. martinezi female, holotype (21); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (22). P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (23); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376931/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1454,2022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1926,1949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Wings</emphasis>
. Both Fw and Hw with pale apical areas, with venation white reaching level of RP3 (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1329,1925,1950]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[207,1393,228,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 32. P. minimum, sp. nov. male, holotype, Fw non saturated (29), saturated (30). P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Hw non saturated (31). P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype, Hw non saturated (32)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376933/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="498">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Area of Fw bluish white with space posterior to RA blue, and that of Hw bluish white. Pseudostigma in both wings blue with nine cells in Fw and in Hw. At high saturation, both pale area and pseudostigma becomes more intense blue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
Venation: Px in Fw 33, in Hw 29. RP 
<quantity box="[572,615,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="6" pageNumber="499" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
Fw arising at level of Px 8, in Hw at Px 9. IR1 arising near Px 
<quantity box="[1331,1388,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" pageId="6" pageNumber="499" unit="in" value="13.0">13 in</quantity>
Fw, Px 
<quantity box="[187,243,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="6" pageNumber="499" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
Hw. RP2 both wings branching from RP at less than half distance from subnodus to tip of wing. In Fw and Hw petiolation distal to CuP by a distance about 
<date box="[699,734,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">5X</date>
the length of CuP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis box="[199,252,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Legs</emphasis>
. Femora flexural surface yellow, extensor surface brown; tibiae flexural surface brown, extensor surface yellow. Tarsi black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis box="[199,305,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Abdomen</emphasis>
. S1–7 dorsally black, laterally yellow. S8–9 blue, S10 dorsally blue, laterally brownish yellow. Cercus black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Structural characters.</emphasis>
Median and lateral portions of posterior prothoracic lobe not separated and posterior border slightly convex (
<figureCitation box="[428,514,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Supplementary tooth of tarsal claw absent. Cleft of anterior lamina shaped as ogival Gothic arch (
<figureCitation box="[382,468,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Anterior hamuli with ear-like basal plate. End of batilliform lamina hardly visible. Posterior hamuli with apex sclerotized and curved anteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[955,1046,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Penis segment 
<quantity box="[1252,1302,511,536]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="6" pageNumber="499" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
ectal view subquadrate with small tongue-like apical lobe and distolateral tuft of spines (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1124,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); in lateral view with distal and proximal tuft of spines (
<figureCitation box="[468,552,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Penis segment 2 with tuft of spines near the commissure (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1356,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis box="[199,305,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Abdomen</emphasis>
. S10 slightly elevated dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[672,811,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Figs. 56–57</figureCitation>
), hind border with medial concavity (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1324,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
). Cerci in dorsal view convergent distally (
<figureCitation box="[516,598,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,686,692,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,692,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Measurement (mm):</emphasis>
Hw 46, abdomen 65.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,414,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="499">Female:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
